ZCZC OE29
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 202300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING LOW CENTRES WILL BE POSITIONED E OF IBERIA AND ICELAND
HOWEVER MUCH OF PORTPATRICK WILL BE DOMINATED BY A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
EXTENDING NE FM CONTINENTAL EUROPE ACROSS THE UK N SEA AND SCANDINAVIA.
THROUGH WEDNESDAY LOW CENTRE DEEPENS S OF PORTUGAL WHILST HIGH PRESSURE
CENTRE DEVELOPS IN THE N SEA. THIS CENTRE DRIFTS E ACROSS INTO THE UK THURSDAY
BUT CONTINUES TO DOMINATE CONDITIONS ACROSS ALL SEA AREAS WITH LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE NEAR IBERIA SINKING S. FURTHER LOW CENTRE ALSO MOVS NE ACROSS ICELAND.
HIGH PRESSURE PERSISTS FRIDAY WITH CENTRE DEVELOPING IRELAND AS THE ANTICYCLONE
RIDGES N AND E. LOW CENTRES REMAIN TO THE N W AND S OF THE ANTICYCLONE
AND OUTSIDE OF THE UK'S SURROUNDING WATERS. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS
PORTPATRICK THROUGHOUT THIS PERIOD BUT COULD BE STRG FOR A TIME ACROSS S
E ICELAND ON TUESDAY EVENING BEFORE EASING THROUGH WEDNESDAY
